2 Timothy 1:5-7

!! Introduction
All of us are tempted to follow the herd because we are afraid. Fear of man is a very dangerous thing. There are social pressures that weight down on us.

Tonight as we look at 2 Timothy, we will be faced with similar topics.

Timothy seemed like he was struggling with fear of man as seen in 1 Corinthians 16:10. Timothy had the strength and courage from Paul, but what was Timothy without Paul? This is what will be soon the situation of Timothy.

Each one of us we have acted out of fear and danger. Last week, Paul spent a lot of time in the greatness of God as he spends time with Timothy.

We know that God is using people as instruments to hand down that faith. Even in Acts 8:30-31, we see that an Ethiopian handed the faith even as she reads.

Timothy doesn't know if what happened with his grandmother will be with him.

